### =========================
### CANONICAL TAMPER TEST FLOW
### =========================

### Set these once before running this block.
@studentEmail = devika@gmail.com
@studentId = 16
@tamperJobId = 14

### 1) Login as student (copy token to @studentToken at top)
POST http://localhost:8080/auth/login?username={{studentEmail}}&password=dev

### 2) Ensure a company token exists too (copy token to @companyToken at top)
POST http://localhost:8080/auth/login?username=Atlassan&password=admin

### 3) Create a fresh job for this tamper test (admin)
POST http://localhost:8080/jobs
Authorization: {{adminToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Audit Test Job",
  "description": "Used to verify tamper + re-sign flow",
  "company": {
    "id": 3
  },
  "requiredSkills": "Java, Spring Boot"
}

### Copy returned id here
@tamperJobId = 12

### 4) Check current profile integrity (expect CLEAN/UNSIGNED initially)
GET http://localhost:8080/students/me
Authorization: {{studentToken}}

### 5) Admin tampers profile
PUT http://localhost:8080/students/{{studentId}}
Authorization: {{adminToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Devika Tampered",
  "email": "{{studentEmail}}",
  "branch": "AI",
  "cgpa": 6.8,
  "skills": "tampered-data",
  "projects": "tampered-project",
  "resumeLink": "tampered-link",
  "phone": "0000000000",
  "university": "tampered-university",
  "graduationYear": 2028
}

### 6) Student checks profile again (expect TAMPERED)
GET http://localhost:8080/students/me
Authorization: {{studentToken}}

### 7) Student tries to apply (expect 409 conflict while tampered)
POST http://localhost:8080/applications
Authorization: {{studentToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "job": {
    "id": {{tamperJobId}}
  }
}

### 8) Student re-signs profile
POST http://localhost:8080/students/me/resign
Authorization: {{studentToken}}

### 9) Student checks profile again (expect CLEAN)
GET http://localhost:8080/students/me
Authorization: {{studentToken}}

### 10) Student applies again (expect success)
POST http://localhost:8080/applications
Authorization: {{studentToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "job": {
    "id": {{tamperJobId}}
  }
}

### Copy returned application id here
@tamperApplicationId = 16

### 11) Verify created application data
GET http://localhost:8080/applications/{{tamperApplicationId}}/verify
Authorization: {{companyToken}}

### 12) Run TPA audit across all applications
GET http://localhost:8080/tpa/audit
Authorization: {{adminToken}}